The '''[[coat of arms]] of [[Somalia]]''' were adopted on October 10, 1956. The [[Leopard (heraldry)|leopard]]s which support the [[shield]] and the white star were also found on the coat of arms used in [[Italian Somaliland]]. Formerly, the arms of Somalia from June 8, 1919 featured a shield divided horizontally by a wavy white line (Smith, 1980). The top half of the shield was blue, with a leopard in natural color surmounted by a white five-pointed star.
