'''Emirdağ YHT station''', short for '''Emirdağ Yüksek Hızlı Tren station''' ({{lang-tr|Emirdağ Yüksek Hızlı Tren garı}}), is a railway station located north of [[Emirdağ]], [[Turkey]], that is planned to be constructed soonly<ref>{{cite web|title=Bakan Arslan, Emirdağda YHT Durağı Olacak|url=http://www.rayhaber.com/2016/08/bakan-arslan-emirdagda-yht-duragi-olacak/|website=RayHaber|accessdate=18 November 2017|language=Turkish|date=31 August 2016}}</ref>. The station will be located just east of the [[State road D.675 (Turkey)|D.675]] highway near the village of Karağaç, and will service high-speed trains along the [[Polatlı–Izmir high-speed railway]].
The station will become the first railway station in Emirdağ once opened.
