The '''''Liberian Times''''' is a newspaper published in [[Liberia]], based in [[Monrovia]]. The ''Times'' has a long history; its second incarnation existed between February 1928 and September 1929 and was edited by [[J. Clement Gibson, Jr.]].<ref name="Burrowes2004">{{cite book|last=Burrowes|first=Carl Patrick|title=Power And Press Freedom In Liberia, 1830-1970: The Impact Of Globalization And Civil Society On Media-government Relations|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FaEs88IpUzEC&pg=PA188|accessdate=28 April 2012|year=2004|publisher=Africa World Press|isbn=978-1-59221-294-1|page=188}}</ref> It appears to have closed numerous times and restarted, and has since been established in 2005. It is considered one of the top sources for political issues in Liberia and often the first to publish important political letters.<ref name="Streissguth2006">{{cite book|last=Streissguth|first=Thomas|title=Liberia In Pictures|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=P7fA6zZyHc0C&pg=PA35|accessdate=28 April 2012|date=1 February 2006|publisher=Twenty-First Century Books|isbn=978-0-8225-2465-6|page=35}}</ref><ref name="Padmore2007">{{cite book|last=Padmore|first=George|title=The Life and Struggles of Negro Toilers|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_pyLcF3Cmf8C&pg=PA70|accessdate=28 April 2012|date=30 September 2007|publisher=Wildside Press LLC|isbn=978-1-877880-04-9|page=70}}</ref>
